Kim Davies bought Llanwenarth House where Cecil Frances Alexander wrote the lyrics to All Things Bright and Beautiful . 
  He has admitted illegally altering the Tudor manor in rural Wales . 
  Davies installed shiny mosaic bath and crystal chandeliers in the house . 
  He bought the manor for £657,000 in 2006 and spent £1million on renovations . 
  But he has now pleaded guilty to breaking planning laws . 
  Mrs Alexander was staying at the house when she wrote the hymn . 
 